    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-22T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-22T01:00:00-05:00" n="759"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48g/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-22T14:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1920—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 23—5:32 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>456. Under date of 17th Chinese Government announced to various Legations that
                    the consent of Foreign Governments having been obtained maritime customs
                    stations and native customs stations within radius of 50 <hi rend="italic"
                        >li</hi> of former would begin to impose surtax after January 16th, funds
                    thus collected to go to Famine Relief <pb facs="0828" n="730" xml:id="pg_730"/>
                    Bureau, Ministry of Interior, for audit and disbursement. Meeting of the corps
                    20th considered matter, certain Legations such as British and French demanded
                    greater degree of foreign control over disbursements or would withhold assent as
                    already notified Foreign Office. Matter now under discussion with the Chinese,
                    probably will result in arrangement for disbursements through mixed commission
                    [of] Chinese and foreigners. French also desire postponement of imposition [of]
                    tax for further period.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
